ilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Burnell","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): from the Anglo-Norman French personal name <i>Burnel</i>, a metathesized form of Old French <i>Brunel</i>, originally a nickname for someone with brown hair or complexion."],"variants":[]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705182,"age":16,"year":"1066","julianDay":2110409,"title":"Battle of Hastings","description":"Battle of Hastings was fought between the Norman-French army and the battle-wary English army on October 14, 1066. Duke William of Normandy believed he was the rightful king rather than Harold, who had been crowned king several months earlier. Harold was killed in battle and William was crowned king on Christmas Day 1066.","url":"https://www.english-heritage.org.uk/learn/1066-and-the-norman-conquest/what-happened-battle-hastings/","urlTitle":"English Heritage - Battle of Hastings","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705183,"age":36,"year":"1086","julianDay":2117714,"title":"Domesday Book","description":"Domesday Book is Britain's earliest extant public record with information containing land surveys and landholdings commissioned by William I. The book was completed in 1086.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/domesday/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Domesday","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705184,"age":46,"year":"1096","julianDay":2121366,"title":"The Crusades","description":"A series of religious wars between Christians and Muslims, known as the Crusades, occurred between 1096 and 1291, and played a large role in European Christian dominance in the Middle East.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/middle-ages/crusades","urlTitle":"History - The Crusades","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705185,"age":56,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"King Henry I defeated and captured his brother, Robert of Normandy, at the Battle of Tinchebray in 1106. Robert remained in captivity until his death in 1134.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Sir John de Burnell was born about 1050, in Shropshire, England as the son of Robert Burnell. He married Petronell Corbet in 1094, in Buildwas, Shropshire, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died on 14 December 1107, in Buildwas, Shropshire, England, at the age of 58, and was buried in Buildwas, Shropshire, England."},"et":{"about 1050–14 December 1107":"umbes 1050–14. detsember 1107","1050–1107":"1050–1107","1055–1136":"1055–1136","1100–1140":"1100–1140","1103–Male":"1103–Surnud","1030–1087":"1030–1087","about 1050":"umbes 1050","15 November 1087":"15. november 1087","1066":"1066","1055":"1055","1087":"1087","1086":"1086","1096":"1096","1030":"1030","1140":"1140","1094":"1094","1050":"1050","1107":"1107","1106":"1106","1103":"1103","1136":"1136","14 December 1107":"14. detsember 1107","1100":"1100","3 February 1103":"3. veebruar 1103","about 1100":"umbes 1100","Buildwas Abby; Shropshire, England":"Buildwas, Shropshire, England","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","Saint Julian; Shrewsbury, Shropshire, England":"Shrewsbury St Julian, Shrewsbury, Shropshire